cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on video object segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a meta-learning approach, which involves training a base learner and a meta learner, and optimizing the model using a closed form solver. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.MM (multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a mechanism to speed up the training process, which could be relevant to sub-category cs.RO (robotics).
